Ctrl + C in the terminal to interrupt.

python src/mediapipe_app.py

Ctrl + J to open terminal in VS Code.

python src/record_clips.py \
  --subject_id S003 \
  --fatigue drowsy \
  --attention on_screen \
  --glasses none \
  --lighting normal \
  --duration 30 \
  --append_metadata data/metadata.csv



Core Factors for Your Dataset
1. Fatigue / Vigilance State

alert → normal attentive state

mildly_drowsy → slower blinks, relaxed eyelids, some gaze wandering

drowsy → long blinks, partial/closed eyes, nodding head

2. Attention / Task State

on_screen → looking at MacBook screen / camera

distracted → looking away (side, phone, background)

3. Glasses

none → no glasses

clear → clear prescription/blue-light glasses

tinted → sunglasses or lightly tinted lenses

4. Lighting Conditions

bright → well-lit, daylight or strong lamp

normal → typical indoor lighting

dim → low-light room

backlit → strong light source behind you (window, lamp)

5. Environment (optional, if feasible)

indoor (default, desk setup)

outdoor (sunlight, natural light variability)

in_vehicle (parked car, for driver monitoring relevance)